      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Miya Masaoka — ",
          "textSize": "heading-two"
        },
        {
          "text": "Pieces for Plants ",
          "italic": true,
          "textSize": "heading-two"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Japanese-American composer and koto performer known for interdisciplinary works that explore interspecies collaboration, technology, and experimental listening. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In "
        },
        {
          "text": "Pieces for Plants ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "(2000-2012)"
        },
        {
          "text": ", ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "electrodes translate plant electrical activity into sound. The instrument includes philodendron, circuitry, and performer. Humans and plants form a sort of shared sonic system."
